import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x="population", y="engineers", data=data)
    plt.title("What is the correlation between the percentage of engineers and the population?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='engineers', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the percentage of engineers in the states?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['engineers'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['engineers'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='hurricanes', ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="state", y="hurricanes", data=data)
    ax.axhline(y=data['hurricanes'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max hurricanes: {:.2f}'.format(data['hurricanes'].max()))
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
